To determine the monthly payments received at time t if you are reinvesting your returns, you can use the future value annuity formula as follows:

\[ v = p \times \left( \frac{(i+1)^n - 1}{i} \right) \]

Where:
- \( v \) is the future value you are trying to achieve;
- \( p \) is the monthly payment;
- \( n \) is the total number of payments;
- \( i \) is the interest rate per period.

In your case, if you're making 24 payments per year, \( i \) would be 1/24th of the stated annual interest rate of any account you're putting it into.
